{"key":"post-16484271","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>16484271</id>\n<content>There are no exact ratios which work better than any other ratio.&amp;nbsp; It's species dependent and even strain dependent, assuming you have an isolated strain to experiment with.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Bulk substrate ingredients which can grow all by themselves can be used in any quantity you have available.&amp;nbsp; Keep coffee grinds to half or less of any substrate mix, and vermiculite can be used at up to half by volume to provide minerals and water retention.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Don't use blood meal or veg oil despite claims you'll read.&amp;nbsp; I've not seen any good come from those two in any quantity.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>16484335</next>\n<prev>16484233</prev>\n<first>16483543</first>\n<last>16507032</last>\n<when>1341496333</when>\n<utime>07/05/12 04:52 PM</utime>\n</post>"}